# .env.example -- copy to `.env` and adjust for your machine.
#
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# `.env` is gitignored, so anything you put here stays off GitHub.
#
# NOTE: this project currently ships NO secrets -- it is a self-contained
# computational-topology tool with no API keys, tokens, or credentials.
# The settings below are environment-specific build/run knobs, not secrets;
# they live here so each machine can differ without editing tracked files.
# If you ever add a secret (an API token, etc.), put it here.

# --- Runtime ----------------------------------------------------------------
# Where libregina-engine.so lives (Regina-enabled builds only). Needed at run
# time if Regina is installed under /usr/local and not on the default loader
# path (alternatively run `sudo ldconfig /usr/local/lib` once).
LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/usr/local/lib

# --- Build toggles (see README / Makefile) ----------------------------------
# Uncomment/adjust as needed; these are also overridable on the make command
# line, e.g. `make BHRT_HAS_REGINA=1`.
# BHRT_HAS_GMP=1            # exact GMP intersection form (default ON)
# BHRT_HAS_REGINA=1         # Regina backend: lateral 2-4/3-3/4-2 moves, .esig
# BHRT_HAS_CUDA=1           # CUDA GPU move scorer / colouring scan
# CUDA_ARCH=-arch=native    # override if 'native' is rejected, e.g. -arch=compute_90

# --- Optional paths ---------------------------------------------------------
# Regina install prefix, if not /usr/local.
# REGINA_PREFIX=/usr/local
